class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="darling-shine" class="entry-website-title">Darling, Shine!</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-darling-shine-desktop-3840x11750-20240613.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-darling-shine-desktop-3840x11750-20240613.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-darling-shine-desktop-3840x11750-20240613.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Darling, Shine!"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://darlingshine.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://darlingshine.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Australia</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Darling, Shine! is a heartfelt podcast that navigates the raw experiences of womanhood, widowhood, grief, fertility, IVF, and friendship, aiming to reach out to those who may be riding this roller coaster alone. The website layout is spacious, bright, and easy to navigate, offering swift access to the main menu and streaming platforms.</p><p>Additionally, the website boasts a contrasting color scheme that includes pops of fiery orange to highlight navigation points and important headings. Unlike most podcast websites, the Darling, Shine! website has e-commerce features for those interested in buying merchandise.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>Various CTAs are featured across the home page, encouraging visitors to navigate to the podcast, watch filmed episodes, or join the newsletter mailing list. The floating menu features a link to contact information, which is often excluded from podcast websites.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>Listeners must have an account with the preferred streaming services to enjoy the show, as there are no direct streaming tools on the site. The podcast's social media icons are easily overlooked in the footer menu. Lastly, WAVE detected a notable number of contrast errors.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-darling-shine-desktop-3840x11750-20240613.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-darling-shine-desktop-3840x11750-20240613.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>Despite the desktop site incorporating bold headings, it initially feels unorganized and cluttered. This is largely due to the low contrast issues and content-heavy home page, which includes an overview of the hosts and a gallery of their merchandise.</p><p>While there are no direct streaming tools available on the home page, desktop users may appreciate the inclusion of YouTube content, which feels more accessible and easier to digest on larger screens. On Google's PageSpeed Insights, the site scored 61/100 for accessibility and 55/100 for its overall performance.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-darling-shine-mobile-824x11959-20240613.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-darling-shine-mobile-824x11959-20240613.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The hamburger menu tidies up the home page, allowing the logo and hero image to stand out. The rotating banner of streaming platforms does well to draw attention, but linking to another platform may not suit mobile users who prefer listening directly from the home page. Nonetheless, navigation is smooth, and the floating menu and back-to-top button help streamline the mobile scrolling experience.</p><p>On Google's PageSpeed Insights, the mobile site maintains the desktop version's scores, which include 61/100 for accessibility and 55/100 for performance.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="how-to-money" class="entry-website-title">How to Money</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-podcastexamples-betterteam-20240522-desktop-15.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-podcastexamples-betterteam-20240522-desktop-15.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-podcastexamples-betterteam-20240522-desktop-15.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website How to Money"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.howtomoney.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.howtomoney.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Atlanta, Georgia, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Hosted by finance experts, Matt Altmix and Joel Larsgaard, How to Money is an informative podcast that has helped listeners improve their financial literacy since 2018. The website exudes plenty of personality, with playful colors, engaging graphics, and helpful CTAs reinforcing its approachable aesthetic.</p><p>Navigation is intuitive, and visitors can easily find the team's blog and weekly newsletter sign-up. The website also features direct links to the podcast's social media accounts and streaming channels. For added convenience, the home page includes direct streaming tools as well.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The home page includes a floating, drop-down menu, a helpful search tool, and direct links to various streaming platforms. The podcast's social media icons are clearly displayed in the top and bottom-page menus. Moreover, WAVE could not identify any contrast errors.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>While a drop-down menu provides convenience, the options in the main menu lack relevance, as it mainly directs visitors to blog posts. The website does not offer transcripts, show notes, or an up-and-coming podcast schedule. That said, WAVE detected several empty links and an empty button.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-podcastexamples-betterteam-20240522-desktop-15.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-podcastexamples-betterteam-20240522-desktop-15.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>For desktop users, the well-structured layout provides ample breathing room to explore the various sections, which include an interactive overview of the hosts and information about the podcast's blog. Although a floating menu is available to help make browsing smoother, the menu's irrelevant options and lack of an anchor link function make it less intuitive. On Google's PageSpeed Insights, the site scored 91/100 for performance, as well as 89/100 for accessibility.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-podcastexamples-betterteam-20240522-mobile-12.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-podcastexamples-betterteam-20240522-mobile-12.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>With the mobile site, the menu, now tucked behind a hamburger menu, follows a linear structure that's more user-friendly. While the podcast's social media icons remain visible at the top of the page, the mobile site does not include a sticky top menu. Additionally, the awkwardly placed CTA in the header obscures the full potential of the image. On Google's PageSpeed Insights, the mobile site scored 60/100 for performance, but it retains the desktop site's accessibility score of 89/100.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="overdue" class="entry-website-title">Overdue</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-podcastexamples-betterteam-20240522-desktop_2024-05-23-104205_pwag.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-podcastexamples-betterteam-20240522-desktop_2024-05-23-104205_pwag.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-podcastexamples-betterteam-20240522-desktop_2024-05-23-104205_pwag.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Overdue"
