class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>On the desktop version, the hero image lacks impact, as the prominent black space detracts from the website's otherwise colorful aesthetic. Both versions lack a sticky top menu and a back-to-top button, but the absence of these elements is more noticeable on the desktop site, as it slows the scrolling experience and makes the website feel less intuitive. The website performed well on Google's PageSpeed Insights, scoring 93/100 for performance and 95/100 for accessibility.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-betterteam-20240523-mobile-2.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-betterteam-20240523-mobile-2.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile version reduces the amount of empty spaces found on the desktop site, giving it a more structured appearance. Unlike the desktop version, the mobile site omits the section introducing the latest episodes, leaving it up to the listeners to explore further. That said, the hero image is more compact and screen-fitted, allowing visitors to better appreciate the colorful graphic of the hosts.</p><p>On Google's PageSpeed Insights, the mobile site maintains the desktop version's accessibility score of 95/100, but the performance score decreased to 64/100.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="section-content"><div
class="container"><div
class="narrow-container"></div></div></div><div
class="section-faq"><div
class="container"><h2 id=fAQs class="section-heading">FAQs:</h2><div
class="row"><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-are-podcast-websites class="question">What are podcast websites?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Podcast websites are online platforms created by the host or hosts to serve as a dedicated hub for their shows. The website provides listeners with a look behind the scenes, as it typically features show notes, quick descriptions of the latest episodes, and a detailed schedule for upcoming episodes.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-is-a-good-podcast-website-example class="question">What is a good podcast website example?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>We've curated a collection of podcast websites prioritizing functionality and user navigation. Among them, the <a
href="https://www.comingtonewyorkcity.com/">Coming to New York podcast</a> is one of our standout examples, as the website boasts an intuitive design, a cohesive color scheme, an embedded podcast streaming tool, and a clear overview of the host, making it a prime example of a good podcast website.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=how-do-i-create-a-podcast-website class="question">How do I create a podcast website?</h3><div
class="answer"><ol><li>Consider the podcast's theme, the host's personality, and the brand identity.</li><li>Choose a website builder, such as Zarla, for ease of use.</li><li>Customize your website by adding your podcast logo, color scheme, and preferred typography.</li><li>Include essential links, such as those to your streaming platforms.</li><li>Optimize your website for mobile devices to ensure you reach users on various platforms.</li></ol></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=do-i-need-a-website-for-my-podcast class="question">Do I need a website for my podcast?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Yes, having a dedicated website for your podcast is important for several reasons. The website will serve as a centralized hub where listeners can learn about the host(s) and the podcast's theme, find detailed show notes, and access the latest episodes. Additionally, a website improves discoverability through SEO practices, which helps drive organic traffic to the podcast.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-features-should-a-podcast-website-include class="question">What features should a podcast website include?</h3><div
class="answer"><ul><li>Links to streaming platforms.</li><li>Options for direct streaming or downloading.</li><li>Informative episode summaries.</li><li>A weekly or monthly schedule.</li><li>A clear overview of the podcast's theme.</li><li>A contact form/page for feedback.</li><li>Links to the podcast's social media platforms.</li></ul></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=can-i-include-direct-streaming-options-on-my-podcast-website class="question">Can I include direct streaming options on my podcast website?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Yes, you can include direct podcast streaming options on your website. Embedding a streaming player allows visitors to easily listen to episodes directly from the site, removing the need to create accounts on streaming services. This feature also automatically improves the user experience and encourages visitors to stay on the website longer.</p></div></div></div></div></div> <script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What are podcast websites?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>Podcast websites are online platforms created by the host or hosts to serve as a dedicated hub for their shows. The website provides listeners with a look behind the scenes, as it typically features show notes, quick descriptions of the latest episodes, and a detailed schedule for upcoming episodes.<\/p>\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is a good podcast website example?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<p>We've curated a collection of podcast websites prioritizing functionality and user navigation. Among them, the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.comingtonewyorkcity.com\/\">Coming to New York podcast<\/a> is one of our standout examples, as the website boasts an intuitive design, a cohesive color scheme, an embedded podcast streaming tool, and a clear overview of the host, making it a prime example of a good podcast website.<\/p>\n"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I create a podcast website?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"<ol>\n<li>Consider the podcast's theme, the host's personality, and the brand identity.<\/li>\n<li>Choose a website builder, such as Zarla, for ease of use.<\/li>\n<li>Customize your website by adding your podcast logo, color scheme, and preferred typography.<\/li>\n<li>Include essential links, such as those to your streaming platforms.<\/li>\n<li>Optimize your website for mobile devices to ensure you reach users on various platforms.<